        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/dot-decals/top5pct-custom-dot-truck-signs-illinois.jpg"
            alt="Custom DOT truck signs in Illinois"
            title="USDOT Number Stickers and Compliance Requirements"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We print USDOT number stickers and DOT compliance decals for commercial vehicle operators throughout Joliet, Shorewood, Rockdale, and Will and DuPage County. Both owners of <a href="/" class="link-notification">Top 5 Percent</a> drove trucks in the military and one still holds a valid CDL Class A license with over 15 years of tractor trailer driving experience. We are not just a print shop that happens to make DOT stickers, and alongside your compliance markings we can produce a complete branded graphics package using our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team for wraps, lettering, and logo installations. We are a veteran owned business run by people who have personally operated commercial vehicles and understand the compliance requirements that keep truckers on the road and out of trouble with the FMCSA, and for operators who also need a removable sign option for lighter vehicles our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> are a great complement to your permanent truck lettering.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">A USDOT number is the unique identifying number assigned to your commercial vehicle by the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration. This number is used to track safety information during roadside inspections, crash investigations, and audits. Federal regulations require the USDOT number to be displayed in lettering that is at least two inches tall and in a color that contrasts clearly with the background of your vehicle. For most state and local government vehicles, the required minimum size increases to three inches. Non compliance can result in fines, failed inspections, and vehicles being placed out of service until the markings are corrected, and for complete branded graphics that go beyond compliance markings our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team handles full wraps, partial wraps, and vinyl lettering packages that can incorporate your DOT numbers into a polished truck branding layout.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">If your truck also needs full branding graphics beyond compliance markings, our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team handles full and partial wraps on cabs, trailers, and vans. For operators who also run light duty vehicles and want a removable sign option, our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> are a great complement to your permanent truck lettering.</p>
            <p>We print DOT decals the same day in most cases because we understand that a truck sitting in the yard waiting for compliance stickers is a truck that is not earning. We are located at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet and we serve truckers and fleet operators from across Will and DuPage County including Channahon, Minooka, Braidwood, and all the way out to Kankakee. Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> before you head over and we will have your order ready to go as quickly as possible.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/dot-decals/top5pct-dot-decals-semi-truck.jpg"
            alt="Custom DOT decals for semi trucks in Joliet Illinois"
            title="Print and Cut Decals with Clean Professional Edges"
            imagePosition="right"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We produce DOT decals using two methods and the right choice depends on your design and how you want your truck to look. The first method is digitally printed decals. Digital printing produces full color graphics with photographs, logos, gradients, and complex artwork. If your DOT package includes a trucking company logo with multiple colors, a photorealistic image, or any design element that goes beyond simple lettering, digital printing is the right call, and if you need a professional trucking logo built from scratch our <a href="/design-services/logo-design" class="link-notification">logo design</a> team creates scalable vector artwork specifically optimized for truck door applications. We can also apply a protective laminate over digitally printed decals to extend their life and protect the print from fuel, road chemicals, UV exposure, and pressure washing, and for drivers who also need a removable sign option for personal vehicles our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> use the same print quality in a flexible, easy-on easy-off format.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">The second method is vinyl cut decals. Vinyl cut DOT lettering is the most common choice for USDOT numbers, MC numbers, and GVWR markings because it is clean, sharp, and legible at a distance. We use a computer controlled cutter that produces precise edges on every character. The result is a crisp, professional looking set of compliance letters that read clearly from 50 feet, which is exactly what the regulations require. Clean cut edges are not just about appearances. They also extend the life of the decal by preventing moisture from working its way under the vinyl at rough or jagged edges, and for precision die-cut shapes beyond standard lettering our <a href="/stickers/custom-shaped-stickers-decals" class="link-notification">custom shaped stickers</a> use the same computer-controlled cutting process for logos, emblems, and any complex shape that needs to be cut from vinyl.</p>
            <p>Because we are a local printer in Joliet, you do not have to wait for a mail order company to ship your decals and then hope they arrive before your inspection date. You can stop by our shop, place your order, and in many cases take your decals with you the same day. We know what proper DOT lettering looks like, and we will not let a bad looking set of decals leave our shop. Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> to place your order.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.cta-quadruple-button-banner />

        <x-sections.card-2image-with-text
            image1="/images/dot-decals/top5pct-dot-lettering-joliet.jpg"
            alt1="Custom DOT lettering in Joliet Illinois"
            image2="/images/dot-decals/top5pct-dot-magnets.jpg"
            alt2="Custom DOT magnets for trucks in Joliet Illinois"
            title="Trucking Logo Design and Truck Branding"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We design custom trucking logos and truck branding graphics for owner operators and small trucking companies throughout Joliet, Will and DuPage County who want their equipment to stand out from the roughly 16 million trucks on the road in the United States. When most of those trucks are plain and unbranded, a well designed trucking logo and a clean set of door graphics make your rig immediately memorable to everyone who sees it on the highway. Kids chase after trucks with great graphics trying to get the driver to honk. Adults do double takes on the interstate. That kind of attention translates directly into brand recognition for your company and your operation.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">Our design team has over 20 years of experience and has created trucking logos for startups, established carriers, and independent owner operators across the Chicagoland area. A great trucking logo communicates professionalism and reliability, which matters to shippers and brokers evaluating which carriers to work with. We take the time to understand what your operation represents and we build a logo that fits your identity, your equipment color, and the image you want to project on the road. Whether you are just starting out or you are updating an old look that no longer represents where you are today, we are ready to help.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">To extend your brand beyond your truck, we also produce <a href="/custom-apparel/group-wear/corporate-wear-shirts" class="link-notification">corporate wear</a> so your drivers and yard staff represent your company consistently in uniforms that match the look on your doors. We also print <a href="/stickers/standard-stickers-decals" class="link-notification">custom stickers and decals</a> for paperwork, cargo labels, and fleet management applications that carry your logo into every part of your operation.</p>
            <p>We also produce full truck graphic packages that combine your new logo with DOT compliance numbers, MC numbers, company name and address lettering, and any additional design elements that fill out the side of your trailer or cab. A complete, cohesive truck graphic package makes your operation look established and serious. We serve owner operators and small fleet operators in Joliet, Shorewood, Crest Hill, Channahon, Minooka, and throughout Will and DuPage County. Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> to talk about your trucking logo and truck graphic project.</p>
        </x-sections.card-2image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/dot-decals/top5pct-trucking-dot-decals-in-joliet.jpg"
            alt="Custom trucking DOT decals in Joliet Illinois"
            title="MC Numbers, GVWR Markings, and Full Compliance Packages"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We print and apply full DOT compliance packages for commercial vehicle operators in Joliet, Shorewood, Rockdale, and across Will and DuPage County. A complete compliance package for a commercial truck typically includes the USDOT number, the MC number for interstate carriers, the company name and principal place of business, the GVWR or gross vehicle weight rating, and in some cases KYU numbers for carriers operating in Kentucky. We are familiar with all of these requirements and we can help you understand exactly what your specific vehicle and operation requires so you are fully compliant and ready to pass any roadside inspection, and for a complete truck branding package that combines compliance markings with your company logo and door graphics our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team handles the full layout in one visit. If you also need a professional trucking logo built before we print your door graphics, our <a href="/design-services/logo-design" class="link-notification">logo design</a> team creates scalable vector artwork specifically optimized for truck door applications.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">The cost of not having proper DOT markings on your commercial vehicle is significant. Fines start at several hundred dollars per violation and can climb into the thousands for repeat offenses or for vehicles that are operating with no markings at all. A vehicle that fails an inspection for non compliant markings can be placed out of service on the spot, which means your load does not move until the issue is corrected. Our same day service means you can get your compliance markings handled quickly without unnecessary downtime for your operation, and while you are here we can also set up a branded magnet package through our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> team for any light vehicles in your operation that need a removable sign option. We understand that every day a truck is not on the road is money you are not making.</p>
            <p>We also work with local businesses and municipalities in the Will and DuPage County area that operate commercial vehicles and need DOT markings applied correctly and professionally. From work trucks and utility vehicles to box trucks and flatbeds, we produce legible, correctly sized, properly contrasting compliance lettering that meets all current federal and Illinois state requirements. Do not risk a fine or an out of service order over something as preventable as a missing or non compliant DOT number. Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> or visit us at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet and we will take care of you today.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>


    <x-sections.product-grid collectionSlug="dot-decals" parentSlug="vehicle-graphics" />

            <x-sections.card-detailed-info
                heading="Why Do Truck Drivers Need DOT Decals and DOT Stickers?"
                image1="/images/dot-decals/top5pct-article-DOT-decals-vinyl-lettering.jpg"
                alt1="DOT decals DOT stickers and truck lettering printed in Joliet, Will and DuPage County Illinois"
            >
                <x-slot name="intro">
                    <p class="mb-4">DOT decals and DOT stickers are not optional for commercial truck drivers. They are a federal requirement. Any commercial motor vehicle that operates in interstate commerce must display a valid USDOT number, the legal company name, the city and state of the principal place of business, and in many cases the MC number, GVW rating, and KYU number as well. These markings must be legible, in contrasting colors, and visible from 50 feet. They must be at least two inches tall and placed on both sides of the power unit. Failure to display the correct DOT markings can result in fines, out of service orders, and violations that follow your carrier record. We produce DOT decals and commercial vehicle lettering for truckers and fleet operators throughout Joliet, Shorewood, Channahon, Rockdale, and all of Will and DuPage County, and for operators who also want branding graphics alongside their compliance markings our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team handles wraps, lettering, and logo installations in the same appointment.</p>
                </x-slot>
                <x-slot name="mid">
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">We Know Trucking Because We Have Lived It</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Both owners of Top 5 Percent, LLC drove trucks in the military and understand the commercial vehicle world from the inside. One of our owners still holds a valid CDL Class A license with over 15 years of tractor trailer driving experience. When you call us about DOT decals, you are not talking to someone who just prints stickers, and beyond compliance decals we can design a complete truck branding package using our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team that combines your compliance markings with a polished company logo and door lettering. You are talking to a fellow trucker who understands exactly what needs to go on your doors, why it matters, and how to do it right, and for owner operators who want a professional logo built from scratch our <a href="/design-services/logo-design" class="link-notification">logo design</a> team creates scalable vector artwork specifically optimized for truck door applications. We take DOT compliance seriously because we know what is at stake when inspectors pull you over and start checking your markings at a weigh station on I-80.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Vinyl Cut or Digitally Printed: Your Choice</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Not all DOT decals are the same and the right option depends on what you need displayed. Vinyl cut decals are clean, precise, and great for simple number sets and lettering that does not require color fills or complex graphics. The letters and numbers are cut directly from solid colored vinyl and applied individually, giving a professional look that blends well with most truck door colors. Digitally printed decals handle more complex jobs including full color trucking logos, multi-color designs, and complete door graphic packages. We can laminate digitally printed decals for added protection against road debris, fuel spills, and UV exposure so your markings stay legible and compliant for years, and for drivers who also need removable sign options for personal or lighter vehicles our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> use the same full-color print quality in a flexible format that snaps on and off without any permanent installation.</p>
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Same Day Local Service in Joliet</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">Because we are a local print shop based in Joliet, you do not have to wait for a mail order company to ship your decals and then wait again for them to arrive. You can call us, stop by our shop at 121 Springfield Avenue, and in many cases leave the same day with your DOT markings ready to apply. For drivers who are running a tight schedule or need to get a vehicle back on the road fast after a DOT inspection that flagged missing markings, same day service is not just convenient. It is essential. We understand that a truck sitting in the lot is not earning, and we do everything we can to get your vehicle back on the road legally and quickly, and while your truck is here we can also set up any additional branding graphics through our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team so your compliance markings and company branding are both handled in a single visit.</p>
                </x-slot>
                <x-slot name="lower">
                    <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">Everything We Produce for Commercial Vehicles</h3>
                    <p class="mb-4">We produce a full range of commercial vehicle compliance markings and graphics for trucking companies, owner operators, and fleet managers throughout Will and DuPage County and the Chicagoland area. Our services include USDOT number decals, MC number decals, KYU number decals, GVW rating stickers, legal company name and address lettering, <a href="/design-services/logo-design" class="link-notification">trucking logo design</a> and printing, and complete door graphic packages that combine all required markings with your company branding in a single professional layout. We work with single truck owner operators and multi-vehicle fleets and we can match existing door graphics on your other trucks so everything in your fleet stays consistent and compliant, and for drivers who also need a removable sign option for personal vehicles our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> are a great complement to your permanent truck lettering.</p>
                </x-slot>
                <x-slot name="footer">
                    <p class="mb-4">We are a veteran owned print shop in Joliet, Illinois and we are proud to serve the trucking community that keeps the Chicagoland area and the entire country moving. We know what it takes to stay compliant and we are here to make the process as fast and straightforward as possible for every driver and fleet operator who walks through our door, and our full <a href="/vehicle-graphics" class="link-notification">vehicle graphics shop</a> means DOT decals, truck lettering, wraps, and magnets can all be handled in one visit. For owner operators who also want to brand their non-commercial vehicles, our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/vehicle-magnets" class="link-notification">vehicle magnets</a> offer a removable sign option that looks just as professional as permanent vinyl.</p>
                    <p>Call us at <a href="tel:+18153498600" class="link-notification">(815) 349-8600</a> or stop by 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet to order your DOT decals today. We are ready to help you stay on the road and stay compliant, and ask about adding a branding package through our <a href="/vehicle-graphics/automobile-graphics" class="link-notification">automobile graphics</a> team to make your truck look as professional as it performs.</p>
                </x-slot>
            </x-sections.card-detailed-info>

